Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.27,0:00:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(626,558)\i1}To save Tokunosuke, I started a Duel \Nagainst both Droite and Gauche at the same time!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.79,0:00:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(662,556)\i1}But for for some reason, Astral isn't showing himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.09,0:00:11.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(626,546)\i1}Their attacks are coming one after the other!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.34,0:00:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is bad! At this rate, I'll...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.71,0:00:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gagaga Gardna!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.00,0:00:24.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no point in trying to defend your Monster when you have no cards in your hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.28,0:00:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No cards in my hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.86,0:00:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.98,0:00:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Tasuke Knight in my Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.46,0:00:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this card is in my Graveyard while my Monster is attacked when I have no cards in my hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.78,0:00:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I can Special Summon this card and end the battle this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.47,0:00:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.55,0:00:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Monster's attack was stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.73,0:00:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I managed to make it...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.37,0:00:55.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a persistent bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.33,0:00:58.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, it's my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.96,0:01:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have two Level Four Monsters on my field.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.09,0:01:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can just manage to Summon Hope...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.03,0:01:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral!?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.68,0:01:10.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(650,508)}Now, it's your turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.98,0:01:14.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(626,572)\i1}If he's not here, I can't call out Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.28,0:01:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(668,608)}Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.90,0:01:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(608,584)}Where the hell are you looking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.90,0:01:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(692,596)}Be gone, Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.88,0:01:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(656,612)}Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.18,0:01:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(642,616)}Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.50,0:01:41.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go back to Yuma! He needs you!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.24,0:01:50.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think I'll just let you run away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.61,0:01:55.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.81,0:01:59.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if Hope isn't here...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.32,0:02:02.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.79,0:02:07.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This card can't defeat their Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.49,0:02:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I attack Phantom Butterfly Assassin Morpho with Tasuke Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.59,0:02:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell Push!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.97,0:02:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only 500 points?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.27,0:02:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That ain't enough spirit to beat us!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.03,0:02:30.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.05,0:02:33.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go to Hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.78,0:02:45.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.43,0:02:48.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and end your turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.11,0:02:50.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.92,0:02:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll put an end to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.34,0:02:59.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a card face-down...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.75,0:03:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.06,0:03:14.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.13,0:03:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.31,0:03:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why just Hope?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.16,0:03:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral... Are you here, Astral?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.87,0:03:28.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral, did something happen to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.07,0:03:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he got away, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.14,0:03:34.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Astral...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.95,0:03:37.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the only one who could defend you has left.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.45,0:03:41.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The stupid fool left all so he could help out some lowly human.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.01,0:03:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, come to me, Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.83,0:03:49.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will absorb all of you myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.15,0:03:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Numbers!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.45,0:04:03.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now all of them are under my control!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.73,0:04:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you're next, Astral.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.58,0:04:07.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.85,0:04:11.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh-What was the deal with that light just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.53,0:04:14.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something isn't right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.44,0:04:15.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Gauche!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.23,0:04:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like the Hope card has returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.80,0:04:20.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.32,0:04:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you off fighting somewhere or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.31,0:04:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thats why you sent him to me alone...?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.03,0:04:32.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case, I won't let your feelings go to waste!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.51,0:04:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bring it to em!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.78,0:04:39.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay the Level Four Gagaga Gardna and Tasuke Knight!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.00,0:04:44.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I build the Overlay Network with my two Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.57,0:04:46.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.45,0:04:53.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appear, Number 39! Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.52,0:04:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.23,0:04:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.06,0:05:00.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.84,0:05:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Number?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.09,0:05:05.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That kid has a Number!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.53,0:05:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Number 39!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.94,0:05:12.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope, endure it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.30,0:05:16.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a card face-down and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.00,0:05:18.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A Number...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.81,0:05:23.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This thing's become far more interesting!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.65,0:05:24.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Gauche!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.15,0:05:27.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.20,0:05:30.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Moonlit Papillon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.51,0:05:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Droite!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.01,0:05:38.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you he's mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.24,0:05:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't allow that!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.46,0:05:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that we know he possesses a Number, this has become a Duel for Mr. Heartland!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.00,0:05:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a killjoy!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.96,0:05:55.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay the Level Four Phantom Butterfly Assassin Swallowtail and Moonlit Papillon!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.47,0:05:59.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I build the Overlay Network with my two Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.80,0:06:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.63,0:06:04.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appear, Photon Butterfly Assassin!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.31,0:06:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Photon!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.63,0:06:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've never seen such a Monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.18,0:06:14.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This Monster is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.29,0:06:19.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the same type of Monsters Kaito used!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.50,0:06:23.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As I get closer, I stretch my hand out
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.17,0:06:26.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}towards that shining light leading towards tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.39,0:06:33.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I dream of a world that expands from my feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.23,0:06:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I haven't a clue of where things like dreams and hopes are at.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.74,0:06:47.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if I run looking for it, I still can't seem to find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.20,0:06:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder if I have fallen into a gap of truth and lies.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.70,0:06:58.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even so, our grand tale has yet to begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.92,0:07:04.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's move on towards tomorrow, \Neven if our road begins to fall apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.17,0:07:09.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will jump forward, before all my\N strength completely drains.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.85,0:07:12.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The closer I get, the further it becomes,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.43,0:07:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}that truth that I must seize.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.60,0:07:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's to find hope that we desire from a future unseen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.77,0:07:23.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With a heart stronger than anyone else,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.57,0:07:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll learn to keep running up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.86,0:07:32.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With the strength to win any battle, \Ndespite just how weak I am,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.58,0:07:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My purpose is to find,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.58,0:07:37.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}with these invaluable friends of mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.58,0:07:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The future of the world expanding\N from my feet with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.08,0:08:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(452,494)}Number 38: Connect the Hope Together! \NHope Sword Mars Slash!!"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.45,0:08:03.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Photon Monsters just like Kaito?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.49,0:08:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you say Kaito?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.61,0:08:09.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know Kaito?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.89,0:08:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just give it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.68,0:08:16.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Running away is useless!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.30,0:08:21.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will force you to remember our mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.43,0:08:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(656,522)}Why are you asking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.79,0:08:26.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(630,518)}It's obvious that I Dueled him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.80,0:08:28.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(606,524)}It was quite a tiring match, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.44,0:08:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(668,524)}What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.82,0:08:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(660,510)}You fought Kaito on even ground?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.04,0:08:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(618,532)}Why did Kaito fight this kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.70,0:08:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.31,0:08:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What Mr. Heartland told us about...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.66,0:08:45.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Original Number who came to this world from the Astral World?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.35,0:08:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Are you telling me this kid has the Original with him?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.45,0:08:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If not, how can you explain someone like him fighting Kaito evenly?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.28,0:08:57.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's the mood, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.61,0:08:59.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since you seem to know the Original...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.02,0:09:03.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid, I'll be taking that Number back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.01,0:09:05.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's begin the Number hunting!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.17,0:09:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Photon Butterfly Assassin's Monster Effect activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.98,0:09:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching one Overlay Unit, it switches a Defense Mode Monster into Attack Mode,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.52,0:09:19.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and its Attack Power goes down by 600!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.10,0:09:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope is in Attack Mode!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.48,0:09:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Regardless of whether you have the spirit to fortify your defense, it won't work against us!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.93,0:09:32.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I activate the Quick-Play Magic, Berserk Scales!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.74,0:09:38.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This raises the Attack Power of one Monster by 1000 points until the end of this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.40,0:09:41.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An Attack Power of 3100!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.64,0:09:45.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the difference in their Attack Power is 1200 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.73,0:09:48.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if the Number won't be destroyed, you'll still take damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.46,0:09:52.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means, once I take this attack...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.81,0:09:55.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Photon Butterfly Assassin!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.58,0:09:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Attack Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.77,0:09:59.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Butterfly Distortion!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.22,0:10:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.28,0:10:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope's Monster Effect activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.92,0:10:13.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching one Overlay Unit, it negates one Monster's attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.79,0:10:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moon Barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.66,0:10:19.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saved!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.64,0:10:22.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this I end my turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.11,0:10:30.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Monster that has used Berserk Scales' effect has its Attack Power returned to normal with 1000 more points decreased.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.71,0:10:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But by doing this, we now know Aspiring Emperor - Hope's effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.50,0:10:35.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gauche!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.18,0:10:38.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave the rest to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.00,0:10:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to show you some {\i1}real{\i0} spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.04,0:10:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.57,0:10:51.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I release the Level Four Blade Bouncer to Advance Summon the Level Six Phantom Bouncer!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.25,0:10:57.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two Level Six Monsters!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.09,0:11:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Overlay the Level Six Hammer Rush Bouncer and Phantom Bouncer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.68,0:11:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I build the Overlay Network with my two Monsters!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.77,0:11:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Xyz Summon!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.02,0:11:13.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Appear, Photon Streak Bouncer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.89,0:11:18.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An Attack Power of 2700!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.50,0:11:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now it's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.81,0:11:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Photon Streak Bouncer attacks Aspiring Emperor - Hope!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.60,0:11:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take this! Streak Strike!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.78,0:11:33.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope's Monster Effect activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.18,0:11:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moon Barrier!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.42,0:11:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You fell for it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.64,0:11:38.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.76,0:11:41.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Photon Streak Bouncer's effect activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.74,0:11:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By detaching one Overlay Unit, it negates the opponent's Xyz Monster's effect and deals 1000 points of damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.31,0:11:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he wanted me to use Hope's effect for this!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.57,0:11:58.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So instead of you taking 800 points, you'll take an additional 1000 points on top of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.99,0:12:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is over!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.04,0:12:07.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.55,0:12:20.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now I've got you, Astral.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.77,0:12:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're done for.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.07,0:12:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go, Photon Streak Bouncer!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.89,0:12:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Streak Break!!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.12,0:12:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap activate! Damage Diet!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.67,0:12:42.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It halves all damage done to me during this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.28,0:12:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.02,0:12:59.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not done yet! Since Hope's effect has been negated, the battle resumes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.07,0:13:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do it, Photon Streak Bouncer!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.22,0:13:08.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma's about to lose!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.90,0:13:12.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the Original Number belongs to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.11,0:13:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap, activate! Half Unbreak!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.33,0:13:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Monster that has used this effect can't be destroyed by battle this turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.18,0:13:27.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the damage to the player is halved!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.26,0:13:37.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you managed to withstand it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.17,0:13:44.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But now Hope's Overlay Units and your set cards are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.22,0:13:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.89,0:13:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then surrender and hand us your Number.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.10,0:13:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do that, you'll no longer have to suffer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.98,0:13:58.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop kidding me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.29,0:14:03.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As if I'm gonna surrender to people like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.11,0:14:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.70,0:14:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.56,0:14:14.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I lose this Duel, I'm not the only one affected. He'll disappear!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.22,0:14:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let such a thing happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.04,0:14:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I set a card face-down and end my turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.27,0:14:26.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My turn! Draw!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.09,0:14:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Summon Card Car D!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.63,0:14:38.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By releasing this card during the turn the card is Summoned,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.86,0:14:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can draw two cards from my deck!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.99,0:14:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please give me some cards to turn the tables!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.73,0:14:57.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Double Up Chance and Bi-Tension?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.70,0:14:59.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These cards are...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.48,0:15:05.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, think about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.26,0:15:08.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just think. There has to be a way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.72,0:15:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's gotta be a chance here...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.72,0:15:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.16,0:15:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.99,0:15:26.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My, my. So he finally gave up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.08,0:15:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.40,0:15:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he gave up?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.67,0:15:36.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I'll finish you off as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.74,0:15:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.95,0:15:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's useless...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.99,0:15:57.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral... I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.65,0:16:00.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.73,0:16:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't how you Duel, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.70,0:16:04.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.22,0:16:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how much you failed, no matter how much you were laughed at... You never gave up, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.75,0:16:13.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't give up until the very end!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.69,0:16:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring it to em'!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.82,0:16:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kotori... Tokunosuke...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.30,0:16:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right, huh? The match isn't over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.67,0:16:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let myself give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.04,0:16:28.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll win no matter what it takes!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.40,0:16:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bring it to em'!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.18,0:16:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma, I can feel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.54,0:16:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're bringing it to em'!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.21,0:16:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.58,0:17:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My body's been paralyzed!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.73,0:17:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Yuma and I's...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.00,0:17:07.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the power of our bonds!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.30,0:17:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bonds, you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.36,0:17:23.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.42,0:17:28.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're... Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.26,0:17:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've kept you waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.87,0:17:34.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.50,0:17:36.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.65,0:17:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Astral!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.79,0:17:40.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! He's The Original!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.45,0:17:47.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not like I needed you or anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.30,0:17:52.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could've beaten those guys by myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.43,0:17:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you just had to vanish when I needed to feel your presence!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.50,0:17:57.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You went off somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.92,0:17:59.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Both of them against Yuma...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.81,0:18:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The pieces to victory are gathered!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.06,0:18:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your battle wasn't useless.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.66,0:18:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.49,0:18:11.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yuma... Let's win.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.17,0:18:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.74,0:18:19.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go! First I activate the effect of Overlay Eater in the Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.98,0:18:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I activate the effect of Overlay Eater in my Graveyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.97,0:18:25.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Overlay Eater?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.77,0:18:31.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He sent it to the Graveyard to activate the effect of Gagaga Gardna before!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.01,0:18:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I Banish this card in my Graveyard from the game!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.16,0:18:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It absorbs one of the opponent's Xyz Monster's Overlay Units,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.22,0:18:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and makes it my own Xyz Monster's Overlay Unit!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.63,0:18:50.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now Photon Streak Bouncer's effect has been stopped!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.67,0:18:53.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you're that fired up, it's way too late!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.08,0:18:58.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope, attack Photon Butterfly Assassin!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.13,0:19:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even so, it's only 800 points of damage!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.00,0:19:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aspiring Emperor - Hope's Monster Effect activates!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.97,0:19:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It negates one Monster's attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.10,0:19:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Negating your own attack!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.00,0:19:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From my hand, I activate the Quick-Play Magic, Double Up Chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.88,0:19:23.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If a Monster's attack was negated, that Monster can attack once more with its Attack Power doubled!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.38,0:19:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope's Attack Power doubled!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.12,0:19:29.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's still not enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.83,0:19:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, from my hand I activate the Quick-Play Magic, Bi-Tension!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.59,0:19:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If a Monster attacks more than once, its Attack Power is doubled once more!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.02,0:19:44.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,7600 Attack Points?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.40,0:19:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.66,0:19:46.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, Yuma!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.70,0:19:47.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.51,0:19:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hope Sword Mars Slash!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.39,0:19:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Trap, activate! Bouncer Guard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.71,0:20:04.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It switches a Monster's Attack Target to a Monster with "Bouncer" in its name!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.64,0:20:25.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.03,0:20:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He won, Yuma won!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.16,0:20:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.82,0:20:30.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In that situation, he managed to do a counter-attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.24,0:20:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Astral really is a Dueling genius after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.59,0:20:35.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.61,0:20:39.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did you defend me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.18,0:20:41.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heh, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.63,0:20:43.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was just in the mood to.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.55,0:20:45.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.38,0:20:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Astral really is something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.45,0:20:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hey kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.35,0:20:51.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As promised, we'll forget about your cheating friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.65,0:20:55.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you better remember that I'm gonna beat you next time!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.57,0:20:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Along with the Original Number!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.43,0:21:05.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting! I'll be your opponent anytime!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.22,0:21:09.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like that spirit of yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.06,0:21:13.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what's done is done.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.09,0:21:17.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The rest is gonna be a breeze for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.23,0:21:20.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.04,0:21:21.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you trick us!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.69,0:21:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Return my Heart Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.72,0:21:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.77,0:21:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.75,0:21:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was really harsh!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.77,0:21:47.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,G-Gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.26,0:21:52.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My Heart Pieces... are gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.90,0:21:58.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Droite, don't report what happened today to Mr. Heartland!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.68,0:21:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.34,0:22:01.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll defeat that Original!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.92,0:22:03.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before Kaito does!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.99,0:22:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine then...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.94,0:22:12.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gone...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.67,0:22:16.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please let him have dropped my Heart Piece somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.20,0:22:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cleaning, Cleaning...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.05,0:22:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Someone gave me some water.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.59,0:22:39.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So I was able to paint a rainbow with ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.27,0:22:45.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to become someone perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.85,0:22:48.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it's very difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.23,0:22:51.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even with me suffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.82,0:22:55.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I can't seem to grasp victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.66,0:22:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I want to bloom!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.12,0:23:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I must be having some kind of weird dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.04,0:23:06.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But If I must fulfill this,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.58,0:23:09.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then I don't mind being laughed at for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.54,0:23:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Since it's because your limits are decided on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.76,0:23:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll show it, overcoming it to tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.76,0:23:23.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ah, I'm aiming for the big blue sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.18,0:23:25.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}For all of its glory.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.91,0:23:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The Freesia of Desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.49,0:23:33.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All of those countless flower petals
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.32,0:23:36.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}They came at the expense of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.99,0:23:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}me being able to reach those heights.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.10,0:23:44.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ah, even though I lost my way today,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.33,0:23:46.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I still yearn for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.00,0:23:48.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That Freesia of Desire.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.61,0:23:53.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some dogs appeared out of nowhere and stole my Heart Pieces!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.86,0:23:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I don't get 'em back, I'll be disqualified from the Duel Carnival!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.95,0:23:59.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Yu-Gi-Oh! ZeXal!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.87,0:24:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fated Showdown! Cat-{\i1}chan{\i0} VS Dog-{\i1}chan{\i0}"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.00,0:24:04.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna bring it to 'em!
